This paper discusses the management of an online community, which involves aspects of computer systems (cs.CY), social networks (cs.SI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of technological systems to mitigate norm violations, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CC). Finally, the paper analyzes the qualitative data collected from interviews, which could be classified under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD) as it involves the analysis of human behavior in the context of a software system.
